1
00:00:06,506 --> 00:00:08,341
I think Sakura-kun will be a good fit.

2
00:00:10,343 --> 00:00:11,594
What?

3
00:00:11,678 --> 00:00:13,346
Hold on a second!

4
00:00:13,430 --> 00:00:15,640
Oh, so that's what
you were gonna say?

5
00:00:16,349 --> 00:00:19,853
Then I also think
Sakura-san would be great.

6
00:00:19,936 --> 00:00:21,855
You were cool on your first day,

7
00:00:21,938 --> 00:00:24,607
and you really showed us
your stuff yesterday.

8
00:00:24,691 --> 00:00:25,859
I vote for you, too.

9
00:00:26,401 --> 00:00:27,861
You too? What are you saying...

10
00:00:27,944 --> 00:00:29,112
Same here!

11
00:00:29,195 --> 00:00:30,947
I'm voting for Sakura-chan, too.

12
00:00:31,031 --> 00:00:32,365
Me too!

13
00:00:32,991 --> 00:00:34,367
I vote for Sakura-san!

14
00:00:34,451 --> 00:00:36,161
Hold on, you guys.

15
00:00:36,995 --> 00:00:39,456
That guy's more fit for a role like this!

16
00:00:40,165 --> 00:00:40,999
NO MOTIVATION - IGNORE

17
00:00:41,082 --> 00:00:43,877
He's not the type
who'd like to do stuff like this.

18
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:45,295
Neither am I!

19
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:48,798
Besides, I don't even know
what I'm supposed to do.

20
00:00:48,882 --> 00:00:51,301
Plus, I'm an outsider.

21
00:00:52,385 --> 00:00:54,262
What does that matter?

22
00:00:55,013 --> 00:00:57,182
You're here now, anyway.

23
00:00:57,265 --> 00:01:00,143
And you and Sugishita saved
that middle school boy, right?

24
00:01:00,226 --> 00:01:03,521
And you wiped the floor
with Shishitoren's second-in-command.

25
00:01:03,605 --> 00:01:04,522
Besides...

26
00:01:04,731 --> 00:01:07,901
the three strongest guys in
our class are voting for you.

27
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:09,277
We have no complaints.

28
00:01:11,613 --> 00:01:12,822
Sakura-kun.

29
00:01:12,906 --> 00:01:15,867
If you're up for it,
I'll be your vice-captain.

30
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:17,869
As for the other one...

31
00:01:18,369 --> 00:01:21,581
-How about you, Nirei-kun?
-What? Me?

32
00:01:22,415 --> 00:01:23,541
Moreover...

33
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:26,377
everyone here insists
you should be our leader.

34
00:01:27,003 --> 00:01:28,880
Do you still want to turn us all down?

35
00:01:31,049 --> 00:01:35,345
<i>Grade captain is like
the class's top, right?</i>

36
00:01:35,553 --> 00:01:38,848
It's just that I had something
I wanted to do by becoming the top.

37
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:43,686
<i>I only thought of becoming the top
so I could accept myself.</i>

38
00:01:44,312 --> 00:01:47,148
<i>I don't have anything else
I want to do besides that.</i>

39
00:01:48,316 --> 00:01:50,693
<i>I've been thinking about it
since that day...</i>

40
00:01:50,777 --> 00:01:51,736
<i>I...</i>

41
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:55,240
<i>might just be the same as him.</i>

42
00:01:56,533 --> 00:01:59,244
<i>And yet... they choose me?</i>

43
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:07,836
What are you punks
wasting my time for?

44
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:10,088
We're not telling you
to represent the school!

45
00:02:10,171 --> 00:02:14,342
Don't take so freaking long
just to decide a goddamn grade captain!

46
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:19,514
Who gives a crap? It doesn't
matter all that much who does it!

47
00:02:19,597 --> 00:02:22,308
Aren't you a little too loud?

48
00:02:22,392 --> 00:02:24,060
That was so sudden,
it surprised me.

49
00:02:24,144 --> 00:02:25,103
Like I said!

50
00:02:25,186 --> 00:02:26,813
Just pick someone already.

51
00:02:26,896 --> 00:02:29,149
<i>He was listening to us
through that loud music?</i>

52
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:32,193
-Hey, you.
-Huh?

53
00:02:32,277 --> 00:02:33,820
You do it.

54
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:35,446
There, we're done.

55
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:36,447
Huh?

56
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:39,075
Huh? Why do you decide?

57
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:42,287
It looks like the class
is voting for you.

58
00:02:42,620 --> 00:02:44,581
So why do you keep draggin' this on?

59
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:46,958
<i>So he didn't hear us at all...</i>

60
00:02:47,375 --> 00:02:50,587
Nobody expects you to be
perfect at it from the start.

61
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:53,756
And if you won't do it,
somebody else will do.

62
00:02:54,215 --> 00:02:55,967
There! We're done!

63
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:58,678
Hey, you're the grade captain, aren't you?

64
00:02:58,761 --> 00:03:00,638
Why are you letting him take the lead?

65
00:03:00,722 --> 00:03:02,432
Wha... Sakura-san!

66
00:03:02,891 --> 00:03:05,894
Huh? The hell are you sayin'?

67
00:03:05,977 --> 00:03:08,938
Tamon Team's second-year
grade captain is him...

68
00:03:10,064 --> 00:03:12,400
Ren Kaji!

69
00:03:13,610 --> 00:03:16,487
<i>This guy's the grade captain?</i>

70
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:49,914
<i>This guy...</i>

71
00:04:50,456 --> 00:04:52,166
<i>is the second-year's grade captain?</i>

72
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:56,838
There you have it, Tamon Team
first-year's grade captain is Sakura!

73
00:04:56,921 --> 00:05:00,258
Huh? Hold on a second!
I haven't said I'm doing it!

74
00:05:00,341 --> 00:05:02,010
Besides, how do you know my name?

75
00:05:02,093 --> 00:05:05,430
You're the one who said the grade
captain should be the one to lead.

76
00:05:05,513 --> 00:05:09,350
And said grade captain made the call.
We've gotta follow his order.

77
00:05:09,684 --> 00:05:11,019
DAMN...

78
00:05:11,436 --> 00:05:12,520
It'll be all right.

79
00:05:12,603 --> 00:05:15,398
We aren't saying you should
do everything yourself.

80
00:05:15,481 --> 00:05:16,941
You've got us too.

81
00:05:18,026 --> 00:05:19,652
You heard him, Sakura-kun.

82
00:05:19,902 --> 00:05:22,613
Letting other people show their stuff
is my virtue.

83
00:05:22,697 --> 00:05:25,116
Although I'm not your vice,
I'll still help you!

84
00:05:25,199 --> 00:05:28,619
Yup, yup! Since we're making you
deal with those stuff.

85
00:05:28,703 --> 00:05:30,580
You jerk, so that's what you're after!

86
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:33,458
You don't have to think
too hard about it.

87
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:37,712
The grade captain is still
one of the members of the class.

88
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:40,465
Just take it easy.

89
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:45,845
UGH...

90
00:05:46,179 --> 00:05:49,140
There you have it, Sugishita-kun.
Let's all get along!

91
00:05:51,225 --> 00:05:52,393
Oh, he's sleeping.

92
00:05:52,810 --> 00:05:54,604
Um. Excuse me!

93
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:57,356
Can we make a Tamon Team
first-years chat group?

94
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:58,691
Yeah! Let's go for it!

95
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:00,234
Give me your ID!

96
00:06:00,318 --> 00:06:02,028
I'll mass invite everyone!

97
00:06:02,111 --> 00:06:04,322
Sakura, Suo, Nirei.

98
00:06:04,405 --> 00:06:07,200
We'll give you us second-years' IDs.

99
00:06:07,283 --> 00:06:08,117
GROUPS 2
FRIENDS 38

100
00:06:08,201 --> 00:06:10,870
Whoa! The second-years' contact address!

101
00:06:11,496 --> 00:06:12,789
Good for you.

102
00:06:14,415 --> 00:06:16,209
The class here...

103
00:06:16,834 --> 00:06:18,836
sure has a bunch of good guys.

104
00:06:19,587 --> 00:06:21,839
You gotta lead 'em well.

105
00:06:22,507 --> 00:06:24,383
Lead them?

106
00:06:24,842 --> 00:06:26,469
What am I even supposed to do?

107
00:06:26,552 --> 00:06:28,513
Well, for starters...

108
00:06:28,596 --> 00:06:30,640
just lead them however you want.

109
00:06:31,516 --> 00:06:35,228
<i>But I don't have things I want to do...</i>

110
00:06:38,689 --> 00:06:41,484
Tamon Team's got the patrol duty today.

111
00:06:42,068 --> 00:06:44,695
You newbie captains go follow Kaji.

112
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:53,371
<i>Watch how our second-year leader
does his job up close.</i>

113
00:06:53,454 --> 00:06:56,791
Sakura-san, you don't have
to glare at him like that.

114
00:06:56,874 --> 00:06:58,835
Huh? I'm not glaring at him.

115
00:06:59,418 --> 00:07:01,462
But, I mean...

116
00:07:02,004 --> 00:07:04,423
<i>Kaji-san was apparently
quick to jump into fights</i>

117
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:07,426
<i>and hard to handle
when he was in middle school.</i>

118
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:11,848
<i>We don't know just what could
set him off, like in the classroom.</i>

119
00:07:11,931 --> 00:07:13,850
<i>So it's better not to irritate him.</i>

120
00:07:14,142 --> 00:07:15,143
Kaji-kun!

121
00:07:18,771 --> 00:07:19,689
What's the matter?

122
00:07:19,981 --> 00:07:24,318
My girl Risa-chan has
gone missing again.

123
00:07:24,902 --> 00:07:26,195
A lost child?

124
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:27,822
Huh? Again?

125
00:07:27,905 --> 00:07:29,824
I told you to look after her properly.

126
00:07:29,907 --> 00:07:33,870
I'm sorry. I was careless.

127
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:37,957
Good grief, stop crying.

128
00:07:38,666 --> 00:07:40,460
We'll do something about it.

129
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:46,174
Are there any details on her looks?

130
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:48,676
She's wearing a pink ribbon today.

131
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:49,802
Got it.

132
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:53,681
She might have gone home already,
so you should get home now, Granny.

133
00:07:53,764 --> 00:07:54,599
Got it?

134
00:07:54,682 --> 00:07:57,393
Thank you! Thank you!

135
00:07:59,562 --> 00:08:02,148
Kusumi, take care of it.

136
00:08:05,776 --> 00:08:06,903
EVEN THOUGH A CHILD
WENT MISSING...?

137
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:08,613
He gave the job to someone else?

138
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:12,200
<i>He's not going to do anything himself?</i>

139
00:08:12,742 --> 00:08:16,162
<i>Is that what a grade captain,
a leader, is supposed to act?</i>

140
00:08:16,245 --> 00:08:17,914
<i>I thought a leader is more...</i>

141
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:27,757
It looks like he just forwarded
the info over. He's quick.

142
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:31,469
But it still worries me.
We need to find the kid soon.

143
00:08:31,552 --> 00:08:32,929
You bet.

144
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:35,890
We must find her no matter what.

145
00:08:40,728 --> 00:08:42,813
{\an8}HAYATO SUO: WE MUST FIND THE LOST CHILD
NO MATTER WHAT! ...SAID OUR GRADE CAPTAIN.

146
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:45,900
Who said you should do that?

147
00:08:45,983 --> 00:08:48,903
It's fine, isn't it?
I'm sure everyone will be hyped to help.

148
00:08:48,986 --> 00:08:53,157
But if nobody responds,
I'll just embarrass myself!

149
00:08:53,241 --> 00:08:54,909
{\an8}GOT IT! - OF COURSE!
YESSIR!

150
00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:56,744
TAIGA TSUGEURA: NOW THAT'S SAKURA-KUN!
YOUR ANOTHER VIRTUE!

151
00:08:56,827 --> 00:08:59,413
See? Everyone's hyped up.

152
00:08:59,497 --> 00:09:01,415
Is something the matter, Sakura-san?

153
00:09:01,499 --> 00:09:02,875
Your face is red.

154
00:09:02,959 --> 00:09:04,377
He's embarrassed.

155
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:07,255
Who cares about that?

156
00:09:07,338 --> 00:09:08,214
Let's go!

157
00:09:10,174 --> 00:09:11,300
Sakura-san?

158
00:09:11,926 --> 00:09:14,262
Ouch... What was that?

159
00:09:14,345 --> 00:09:15,638
Are you okay?

160
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:20,977
There it is! Over here!

161
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:23,354
Sakura! Grab hold of her!

162
00:09:23,437 --> 00:09:25,606
Huh? Why?

163
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:28,901
That's her! That's Risa-chan!

164
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:29,902
Huh?

165
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:31,946
Catch that cat!

166
00:09:36,659 --> 00:09:38,703
She's already so high up...

167
00:09:38,786 --> 00:09:42,331
There's nothing we can do
if she got up that high...

168
00:09:50,298 --> 00:09:51,799
Argh, damn cat!

169
00:09:51,882 --> 00:09:53,718
Hold up!

170
00:09:54,844 --> 00:09:56,387
He's like a monkey.

171
00:09:56,470 --> 00:09:59,515
-I gotta hand it to you, Sakura-kun.
-Argh!

172
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:03,936
Let's get ahead of them so we can
catch the cat when she jumps down!

173
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,438
Got it!

174
00:10:33,382 --> 00:10:34,508
Hey!

175
00:10:34,592 --> 00:10:36,385
Stupid cat! Not there

176
00:10:47,855 --> 00:10:49,315
Kaji!

177
00:10:49,940 --> 00:10:52,610
Kusumi and you guys
go help get Kaji outta the water!

178
00:10:52,693 --> 00:10:56,030
You call the grandma!
I'll go borrow some towels!

179
00:10:56,113 --> 00:10:56,947
Go!

180
00:10:57,031 --> 00:10:58,074
Got it!

181
00:11:03,704 --> 00:11:05,247
Thank you.

182
00:11:05,331 --> 00:11:07,583
Thank you so much.

183
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:11,337
Nah, we ain't the ones
who caught your cat.

184
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:16,842
Kaji-kun.

185
00:11:17,718 --> 00:11:19,220
Thank you.

186
00:11:19,303 --> 00:11:22,098
Thanks to you,
Risa-chan is back home safe.

187
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:26,560
Don't ever let this happen again.

188
00:11:26,644 --> 00:11:28,562
It'd be too late if anything happened.

189
00:11:29,063 --> 00:11:32,316
You're right. I'll be careful.

190
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:34,860
Boys, please, take this with you.

191
00:11:34,944 --> 00:11:36,904
Thank you for helping my mother.

192
00:11:37,238 --> 00:11:39,532
Huh? Sakura-san?

193
00:11:41,951 --> 00:11:46,288
<i>I only became the top because
everyone supported me.</i>

194
00:11:46,872 --> 00:11:51,085
<i>They agreed with my vision
and wanted to help me.</i>

195
00:11:52,711 --> 00:11:55,131
What is it that you want to do?

196
00:11:56,048 --> 00:11:57,133
Huh?

197
00:11:57,425 --> 00:12:01,512
You became the grade captain because
you have something you want to do, right?

198
00:12:02,179 --> 00:12:03,848
What is it?

199
00:12:07,184 --> 00:12:10,729
Nothing. What the heck
are you talking about?

200
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:14,191
Besides, I didn't become
the grade captain because I wanted to.

201
00:12:14,275 --> 00:12:16,402
Huh? Then why did you become one?

202
00:12:19,029 --> 00:12:21,532
It's because they told me to.

203
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:25,744
<i>That's... just like me.</i>

204
00:12:27,204 --> 00:12:28,038
Then...

205
00:12:28,330 --> 00:12:29,457
Take care of it.

206
00:12:29,999 --> 00:12:33,085
...why does it have to be you?

207
00:12:52,104 --> 00:12:55,608
If I run out of candies,
I can't make them myself.

208
00:12:55,691 --> 00:12:57,234
What?

209
00:12:57,776 --> 00:13:00,362
I can't lead people like Enomoto.

210
00:13:00,446 --> 00:13:04,074
I can't communicate well
with others like Kusumi.

211
00:13:05,201 --> 00:13:06,619
That's why...

212
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:11,248
I always rely on them.

213
00:13:12,291 --> 00:13:13,542
But...

214
00:13:13,626 --> 00:13:16,170
they still rely on me.

215
00:13:19,507 --> 00:13:24,595
That's why I'll do what I can
to live up to their expectations.

216
00:13:25,804 --> 00:13:27,139
That's all.

217
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:30,518
Hey, Kaji!

218
00:13:30,601 --> 00:13:32,770
You're gonna patrol looking like that?

219
00:13:32,853 --> 00:13:34,271
Put on your clothes!

220
00:13:35,356 --> 00:13:38,192
<i>So I don't need to have any goal?</i>

221
00:13:38,275 --> 00:13:40,110
<i>Huh? But...</i>

222
00:13:41,195 --> 00:13:42,988
<i>To answer their expectations...</i>

223
00:13:43,322 --> 00:13:45,574
<i>Is that the thing he wants to do?</i>

224
00:13:47,326 --> 00:13:49,745
<i>To answer expectations... huh?</i>

225
00:13:51,038 --> 00:13:52,414
<i>But, wait...</i>

226
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:54,250
<i>To begin with, I'm...</i>

227
00:13:56,001 --> 00:13:57,044
Sakura-san.

228
00:13:58,337 --> 00:14:00,130
Here's dango from Kikuchiya.

229
00:14:00,214 --> 00:14:02,466
Their dango is delicious!

230
00:14:03,217 --> 00:14:05,135
But, man, you were like a ninja!

231
00:14:05,219 --> 00:14:06,053
CHATTER CHATTER

232
00:14:06,136 --> 00:14:09,682
You were chasing after a cat, after all.
I thought you'd lose her quickly.

233
00:14:09,765 --> 00:14:12,434
If she was a human,
you'd have caught her immediately!

234
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:16,522
You're so amazing, Sakura-san.
I knew we could rely on you.

235
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:21,318
Hey...

236
00:14:22,236 --> 00:14:24,029
The reason you guys...

237
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:27,908
voted for me to be the grade captain...

238
00:14:29,618 --> 00:14:34,498
is it... because you guys... rely on me?

239
00:14:38,502 --> 00:14:40,588
Why, of course, Sakura-kun.

240
00:14:40,671 --> 00:14:42,756
And you should rely on us, too.

241
00:14:43,382 --> 00:14:46,051
You should learn how to fight, first!

242
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:01,275
Goodness, what's the matter, dear?

243
00:15:01,358 --> 00:15:03,235
Huh? Sakura?
What happened?

244
00:15:03,319 --> 00:15:05,613
Whoa, are you feeling sick?

245
00:15:05,696 --> 00:15:07,865
Maybe I gained weight?

246
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:09,909
It's nothing...

247
00:15:10,826 --> 00:15:13,662
I just... tripped, that's all.

248
00:15:14,538 --> 00:15:16,040
You look terrible.

249
00:15:16,123 --> 00:15:17,791
Not getting enough sleep?

250
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:19,627
No...

251
00:15:20,210 --> 00:15:21,795
<i>I can't tell her...</i>

252
00:15:22,421 --> 00:15:26,425
<i>I spent all night thinking
about what I could do...</i>

253
00:15:26,508 --> 00:15:27,885
<i>I can't tell her that!</i>

254
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:31,764
Come to think of it, have you guys
decided on the grade captain?

255
00:15:32,473 --> 00:15:35,351
Whoa! You're really sick, aren't you?

256
00:15:37,102 --> 00:15:38,771
Wait, are you the grade captain?

257
00:15:41,315 --> 00:15:43,108
Surprised?
Well, sorry 'bout that.

258
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:44,526
Huh? Why do you say that?

259
00:15:45,069 --> 00:15:46,695
I think it's great.

260
00:15:51,241 --> 00:15:54,703
I don't think there's anything great
about having a captain

261
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:57,414
who doesn't even know
what he's supposed to do.

262
00:15:57,498 --> 00:15:59,375
If you don't know what you should do,

263
00:15:59,458 --> 00:16:01,543
you should just start with
what you can do.

264
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:03,170
That's exactly what I'm...

265
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:06,340
TURN AWAY

266
00:16:06,757 --> 00:16:08,425
It's none of your business.

267
00:16:11,136 --> 00:16:13,389
"You," huh?

268
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:15,474
Hey.

269
00:16:17,601 --> 00:16:21,689
You know the names and faces
of everyone in your class, right?

270
00:16:21,772 --> 00:16:22,648
Huh?

271
00:16:22,731 --> 00:16:25,693
Oh, what? You don't?

272
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:28,195
Goodness, how rude of me!

273
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:33,659
Then learning their names
is one thing you can start with.

274
00:16:33,742 --> 00:16:35,911
And make sure you call them
by their names.

275
00:16:36,662 --> 00:16:41,667
Saying their name is a declaration
that you're facing that person properly.

276
00:16:42,626 --> 00:16:44,169
<i>Come to think of it...</i>

277
00:16:45,087 --> 00:16:49,008
<i>Have I called anyone by their name before?</i>

278
00:16:49,591 --> 00:16:51,343
That includes me.

279
00:16:51,427 --> 00:16:53,345
You never called me by my name.

280
00:16:53,429 --> 00:16:54,346
STARE

281
00:16:54,430 --> 00:16:55,848
Huh?

282
00:16:55,931 --> 00:16:58,142
Let's practice!

283
00:16:58,225 --> 00:16:59,393
"Kotoha-chan!"

284
00:16:59,476 --> 00:17:00,352
Come on!

285
00:17:00,436 --> 00:17:01,270
I'm Chiyoko!

286
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:02,187
HMPH

287
00:17:02,271 --> 00:17:03,939
Nobody was asking!

288
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:05,899
Come on, come on!

289
00:17:09,778 --> 00:17:10,988
Thanks for the food!

290
00:17:11,071 --> 00:17:12,406
Ah, he ran.

291
00:17:13,282 --> 00:17:14,992
He must be embarrassed.

292
00:17:17,870 --> 00:17:20,414
I don't think that's the only reason.

293
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:22,791
I think...

294
00:17:24,293 --> 00:17:25,878
he's scared...

295
00:17:25,961 --> 00:17:28,589
of being in a close relationship
with other people.

296
00:17:29,798 --> 00:17:31,675
<i>Do your best, Sakura.</i>

297
00:17:35,387 --> 00:17:38,307
The guy with the buzz cut on the right
is Kurita-san.

298
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:41,101
The guy with a manbun
in the middle is Takanashi-san.

299
00:17:41,185 --> 00:17:43,312
And the black mushroom cut
is Kakiuchi-san.

300
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:45,856
Black mushroom?

301
00:17:45,939 --> 00:17:47,858
The one wearing a hoodie.

302
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:51,695
Dammit, I can't memorize
this many in one go!

303
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:54,406
But I'm glad.

304
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:57,242
When you asked me to tell you
everyone's name.

305
00:17:57,326 --> 00:18:00,287
The responsibility
as the grade captain got into you, huh?

306
00:18:00,913 --> 00:18:02,331
That's not it.

307
00:18:02,414 --> 00:18:04,917
I mean, it won't hurt to
at least know their names.

308
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,752
You don't have to be
so embarrassed.

309
00:18:06,835 --> 00:18:09,963
Oh, then what's my name?

310
00:18:10,047 --> 00:18:11,131
What's mine?

311
00:18:11,215 --> 00:18:13,425
Quit badgerin' me!
I'll knock you guys flying!

312
00:18:13,509 --> 00:18:14,551
Okay, next!

313
00:18:14,635 --> 00:18:16,553
-Oh, how mean!
-Oh, how mean!

314
00:18:18,555 --> 00:18:20,224
Next is...

315
00:18:21,225 --> 00:18:22,976
Anzai-san's hurt...

316
00:18:27,397 --> 00:18:29,191
Did something happen to him?

317
00:18:29,274 --> 00:18:31,777
I didn't hear any news
about him, though.

318
00:18:33,654 --> 00:18:36,782
<i>Hey! All first and second year
grade captains and vice-captains</i>

319
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:38,450
<i>gather up on the school roof!</i>

320
00:18:38,534 --> 00:18:42,371
<i>Umemiya! I told you you're gonna
startle 'em if you start without warning!</i>

321
00:18:42,454 --> 00:18:45,415
<i>Oh, that ding dong, dang dong thingy?</i>

322
00:18:45,499 --> 00:18:47,417
<i>-Which button?
-Too late for that now!</i>

323
00:18:47,501 --> 00:18:49,962
Just ban him from
the broadcast room already.

324
00:18:50,045 --> 00:18:52,214
We're already being called upon, huh?

325
00:18:52,297 --> 00:18:53,799
The first thing in the morning?

326
00:18:53,882 --> 00:18:55,551
What could it be about?

327
00:18:55,634 --> 00:18:58,720
Let's hurry and get going,
Sakura-san, Suo-san!

328
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:01,014
I get it! You don't have to pull me!

329
00:19:01,098 --> 00:19:02,975
-See you!
-See you!

330
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:10,023
Everyone's already here!

331
00:19:11,024 --> 00:19:13,152
Huh? Isn't that Sugishita-san?

332
00:19:13,485 --> 00:19:15,487
No wonder he wasn't in the classroom.

333
00:19:15,904 --> 00:19:19,199
Hey, Sakura, Nirei, Suo.
Over here.

334
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:22,828
What are we doing so early in the morning?

335
00:19:22,911 --> 00:19:26,248
It's a meetin' to see
all of the new captains.

336
00:19:26,331 --> 00:19:30,627
That bein' said, most second-year captains
were the captains in their first year.

337
00:19:30,711 --> 00:19:34,464
The first-years are all kids
who were famous in middle school.

338
00:19:34,548 --> 00:19:36,466
Everyone here knows each other.

339
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:39,720
Do you know them too, Suo-san?

340
00:19:40,888 --> 00:19:42,055
Let's see...

341
00:19:42,139 --> 00:19:45,100
Not exactly everyone,
but I've talked with several of them.

342
00:19:45,559 --> 00:19:49,813
I have to learn the names of
everyone in the class, plus these?

343
00:19:49,897 --> 00:19:52,232
You don't have to, Sakura-san.

344
00:19:52,482 --> 00:19:55,485
If you don't know someone,
I'll tell you about them.

345
00:19:56,945 --> 00:19:59,114
I'll give you a quick rundown first.

346
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:00,824
The guy in a red shirt there...

347
00:20:00,908 --> 00:20:02,659
Hold on a minute.

348
00:20:02,743 --> 00:20:05,078
You know all the grade captains
in the school?

349
00:20:05,162 --> 00:20:07,080
Oh, no...

350
00:20:07,164 --> 00:20:10,959
I simply know all the names and faces
of the students here.

351
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:14,588
You memorized them all?

352
00:20:14,671 --> 00:20:17,216
Yes. I borrowed the
student list yesterday.

353
00:20:17,674 --> 00:20:20,552
I can't be much help in fights,

354
00:20:20,636 --> 00:20:24,223
but I'm relatively good at
remembering names and faces.

355
00:20:24,723 --> 00:20:26,350
I figured if I memorized them,

356
00:20:26,433 --> 00:20:30,229
I could help make
Sakura-san's life here smoother...

357
00:20:31,688 --> 00:20:35,025
Since I've decided to show you
all the way to the top.

358
00:20:36,818 --> 00:20:38,612
That's impressive, Nirei-kun.

359
00:20:38,695 --> 00:20:40,989
I can't do that in such
a short amount of time.

360
00:20:41,073 --> 00:20:43,075
Oh, no. This is nothing, really!

361
00:20:44,993 --> 00:20:47,871
Let's see. As for me...

362
00:20:48,247 --> 00:20:50,290
How about I handle negotiations?

363
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:55,504
I'm good at making people
accept my terms.

364
00:20:55,587 --> 00:20:58,340
And I can casually extract
information from people.

365
00:20:58,423 --> 00:21:00,425
That's kinda scary.

366
00:21:01,468 --> 00:21:04,304
Well, we should do what we're good at.

367
00:21:05,973 --> 00:21:08,684
<i>These guys are ready
to take anything on with me...</i>

368
00:21:09,393 --> 00:21:11,687
<i>They know full well
what they can do.</i>

369
00:21:11,770 --> 00:21:12,604
{\an8}CONFIDENTIAL

370
00:21:12,688 --> 00:21:14,189
{\an8}<i>And put them into action.</i>

371
00:21:16,024 --> 00:21:18,652
Well, I'll count on you guys
on that.

372
00:21:19,778 --> 00:21:21,905
Nirei, Suo.

373
00:21:23,991 --> 00:21:26,076
Huh?

374
00:21:26,159 --> 00:21:29,037
Thank goodness, you remembered our names.

375
00:21:29,121 --> 00:21:30,664
Of course I do!

376
00:21:30,747 --> 00:21:33,542
Sorry guys, we're late.

377
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:35,961
Ugh, there are more of them?

378
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:43,593
Hey, just how many
grade captains are there?

379
00:21:43,677 --> 00:21:46,555
Those people aren't the grade captains!

380
00:21:53,061 --> 00:21:57,357
They're the Four Kings of Furin High
and their advisers!

381
00:23:31,910 --> 00:23:32,869
{\an8}Anzai...

382
00:23:33,870 --> 00:23:35,831
{\an8}Kurita...

383
00:23:35,914 --> 00:23:37,165
{\an8}Takanashi...

384
00:23:37,249 --> 00:23:38,125
{\an8}STARE

385
00:23:38,208 --> 00:23:40,168
{\an8}What are you mumbling about to yourself?

386
00:23:40,252 --> 00:23:42,254
{\an8}It's nothing!

387
00:23:43,213 --> 00:23:45,173
{\an8}<i>I heard him clear enough, though.</i>

